# GLM Provider (z.ai)

## Endpoints

- General: `https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4`
- Coding Plan: `https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4` — required for
  `glm-5.2`. The default in `index.ts` is the general endpoint; the
  active connection's `baseURL` is set in `config.json`.

## `generateObject` must disable thinking + tolerate fences

GLM-5.2 wraps JSON in ```json fences. The OpenAI SDK's
`chat.completions.parse()` strict-parses internally and rejects fences
before any repair logic runs. So `glmLLM.ts` overrides `generateObject`
to:

- use `chat.completions.create` (returns raw content), not `.parse()`
- inject `thinking: { type: 'disabled' }` — the classifier, widgets, and
  the LLM-as-judge reranker don't need to reason; this keeps them fast
- run `repairJson(content, { extractJson: true })` then `JSON.parse`
- validate with `input.schema.parse(...)`

Keep this override. Any new structured-output call on GLM goes through it.

## Model list must match z.ai

z.ai serves: `glm-4.5`, `glm-4.5-air`, `glm-4.6`, `glm-4.7`, `glm-5`,
`glm-5-turbo`, `glm-5.1`, `glm-5.2`. `defaultChatModels` in `index.ts`
must stay synced to this list. Do not list `glm-4-flash`, `glm-4-plus`,
`embedding-3`, etc. — they return `1211 Unknown Model` on z.ai.

The `[1m]` suffix (e.g. `glm-5.2[1m]`) is a Claude-Code-specific alias,
not a valid raw API model id — don't use it here.

## z.ai has no embeddings

Never point the GLM provider at an embedding model. Embeddings go through
Gemini (see `modeModels.ts` `EMBEDDING_MODEL`).

## `streamText` reasoning

GLM-5.2 streams `delta.reasoning_content`. `OpenAILLM.streamText`
(inherited) captures it as `reasoningChunk`. Don't strip it — the UI
research trace depends on it.
